ing an integer; specifies the minimum zoom level at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which to create vector tiles. The default value is 0.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNShapeSourceOptionBuffer":{"type":"topic","title":"MLNShapeSourceOptionBuffer","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNShapeSourceOptionBuffer"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshapesourceoptionbuffer","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSourceOptionBuffer","abstract":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSNumber","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" object containing an integer; specifies the size of the tile","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"buffer on each side. A value of 0 produces no buffer. A value of 512 produces a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"buffer as wide as the tile itself. Larger values produce fewer rendering","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"artifacts near tile edges and slower performance. The default value is 128.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"MapLibre","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNShape":{"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshape","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"MLNShape","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is an abstract class that represents a shape or annotation. Shapes","type":"text"